The author isn't Xu Zhimo

368
00:12:59,879 --> 00:13:01,200
It's Bian Zhilin

369
00:13:02,139 --> 00:13:03,220
So much for "classy"

370
00:13:05,860 --> 00:13:06,559
Again

371
00:13:06,559 --> 00:13:07,480
Listen to this part again

372
00:13:08,419 --> 00:13:10,440
After the Spring Festival of 1992,

373
00:13:10,539 --> 00:13:13,639
Mr. Jia and I flew to Shenzhen for the first time.

374
00:13:14,039 --> 00:13:16,700
The free Maotai served on the plane...

375
00:13:17,000 --> 00:13:19,379
Mr. Jia got dead drunk.

376
00:13:19,899 --> 00:13:20,440
That's right.

377
00:13:21,039 --> 00:13:22,779
I remember this very clearly.

378
00:13:22,860 --> 00:13:23,480
Maotai.

379
00:13:23,679 --> 00:13:24,440
It was definitely Maotai.

380
00:13:24,519 --> 00:13:25,259
Can't be wrong.

381
00:13:25,539 --> 00:13:26,679
Actually, it is wrong.

382
00:13:27,240 --> 00:13:29,240
Free Maotai on planes...

383
00:13:29,240 --> 00:13:30,179
that part is true.

384
00:13:30,379 --> 00:13:31,639
But in the late 80s,

385
00:13:31,759 --> 00:13:32,519
it was discontinued.

386
00:13:34,679 --> 00:13:35,100
Look it up.

387
00:13:36,879 --> 00:13:38,200
Hey, don't you have anything better to do?

388
00:13:38,879 --> 00:13:40,039
Why are you causing trouble here?

389
00:13:40,279 --> 00:13:41,259
Get out.

390
00:13:41,279 --> 00:13:42,480
Me, get out?

391
00:13:44,279 --> 00:13:45,740
This is my room too.

392
00:13:45,820 --> 00:13:46,960
Where am I supposed to go?

393
00:13:47,159 --> 00:13:48,220
Stop filming.

394
00:13:49,279 --> 00:13:50,120
I said stop filming.

395
00:13:50,120 --> 00:13:51,500
Do I have to turn off the phone?

396
00:13:53,299 --> 00:13:54,820
Look at you.

397
00:13:55,179 --> 00:13:57,679
You're causing so much trouble for Jingjing.

398
00:13:57,940 --> 00:14:00,480
Couldn't you just stay in that nursing home?

399
00:14:00,480 --> 00:14:02,139
Why did you run over here?

400
00:14:02,539 --> 00:14:03,980
You've been scolding me for ages now.

401
00:14:04,840 --> 00:14:06,480
I'm going easy on you in front of our daughter.

402
00:14:06,679 --> 00:14:07,740
Don't go on and on.

403
00:14:07,740 --> 00:14:08,860
How am I going on and on?

404
00:14:08,860 --> 00:14:10,840
Can you two stop arguing?

405
00:14:11,139 --> 00:14:12,340
You fight as soon as you meet.

406
00:14:12,700 --> 00:14:13,740
Isn't it annoying?

407
00:14:16,080 --> 00:14:16,480
Fine.

408
00:14:17,500 --> 00:14:18,299
Old Bai.

409
00:14:19,080 --> 00:14:19,740
Ma'am.

410
00:14:21,000 --> 00:14:23,980
Can we sit down calmly?

411
00:14:24,720 --> 00:14:25,720
You *are* sitting.

412
00:14:25,960 --> 00:14:26,820
And have a talk.

413
00:14:28,139 --> 00:14:29,960
You were just like this back in the day.

414
00:14:30,720 --> 00:14:32,779
Nothing was ever good enough for you.

415
00:14:32,879 --> 00:14:34,419
Pulling a long face all day.

416
00:14:34,580 --> 00:14:36,259
Like everyone on the street owed you money.

417
00:14:36,320 --> 00:14:37,860
Nonsense. Slander.

418
00:14:38,559 --> 00:14:39,639
When was I ever like that?

419
00:14:40,120 --> 00:14:41,159
Actually,

420
00:14:41,519 --> 00:14:42,080
Mom,

421
00:14:42,340 --> 00:14:43,600
you really were a bit like that.

422
00:14:44,360 --> 00:14:45,879
Our daughter said so, I'm right, aren't I?

423
00:14:46,399 --> 00:14:47,379
Actually, back then,

424
00:14:47,379 --> 00:14:49,080
I put up with you for so long.

425
00:14:49,080 --> 00:14:50,639
I really didn't want to divorce you.

426
00:14:50,799 --> 00:14:51,720
Wasn't it just because back then,

427
00:14:51,720 --> 00:14:53,879
you wouldn't let go of that one little thing?

428
00:14:53,960 --> 00:14:56,820
No matter how I apologized or promised, it wasn't enough.

429
00:14:56,820 --> 00:14:57,840
You insisted on divorcing me.

430
00:14:58,019 --> 00:14:59,179
You apologized?

431
00:14:59,259 --> 00:15:00,200
Admitted your mistake?

432
00:15:00,240 --> 00:15:02,419
Was your apology or promise worth anything?

433
00:15:02,500 --> 00:15:04,620
You were possessed back then.

434
00:15:04,700 --> 00:15:06,080
You were completely deluded.

435
00:15:06,080 --> 00:15:07,159
You were dead set

436
00:15:07,159 --> 00:15:08,759
on leaving with that little vixen.

437
00:15:08,759 --> 00:15:10,820
You dumped us, mother and daughter, just like that.

438
00:15:10,820 --> 00:15:12,039
You're making it up, nonsense.

439
00:15:13,000 --> 00:15:14,000
Am I that kind of person?

440
00:15:14,679 --> 00:15:15,700
Actually,

441
00:15:15,799 --> 00:15:16,279
Dad,

442
00:15:16,919 --> 00:15:18,220
you are exactly that kind of person.

443
00:15:19,460 --> 00:15:20,139
See?

444
00:15:20,399 --> 00:15:21,720
Even our daughter knows about it.

445
00:15:21,779 --> 00:15:22,299
Right?

446
00:15:22,340 --> 00:15:23,379
And you still won't admit it.

447
00:15:23,460 --> 00:15:24,379
Go on then.

448
00:15:24,440 --> 00:15:26,019
Go live with that little vixen.

449
00:15:26,019 --> 00:15:28,179
Why come back to find us?

450
00:15:30,080 --> 00:15:31,200
Well, in the end,

451
00:15:31,340 --> 00:15:32,360
I didn't marry her.

452
00:15:32,440 --> 00:15:34,700
Aren't I still single now?

453
00:15:35,299 --> 00:15:36,480
That's because

454
00:15:36,559 --> 00:15:38,000
you left with absolutely nothing.

455
00:15:38,000 --> 00:15:40,000
She despised you and wouldn't be with you.

456
00:15:40,259 --> 00:15:41,320
That's not true.

457
00:15:41,320 --> 00:15:43,100
Can you two stop arguing?

458
00:15:45,679 --> 00:15:46,740
All these years,

459
00:15:47,279 --> 00:15:48,559
how many times have I dreamt

460
00:15:48,559 --> 00:15:50,419
of our family reuniting?

461
00:15:50,480 --> 00:15:52,360
I even fantasized you two might get back together.

462
00:15:53,139 --> 00:15:54,320
But looking at it now,

463
00:15:54,759 --> 00:15:55,940
forget it.

464
00:15:56,299 --> 00:15:57,659
You fight the moment you meet.

465
00:15:57,659 --> 00:15:58,799
You smash things at the drop of a hat.

466
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:00,460
I remember it all now.

467
00:16:01,659 --> 00:16:03,960
I beg you, don't meet each other anymore.

468
00:16:03,960 --> 00:16:05,360
I really can't handle the embarrassment.

469
00:16:15,200 --> 00:16:16,019
How about...

470
00:16:16,179 --> 00:16:16,759
Old Bai,

471
00:16:17,519 --> 00:16:18,480
we just

472
00:16:19,039 --> 00:16:20,259
shake hands and make peace?

473
00:16:20,740 --> 00:16:21,759
That's good.

474
00:16:22,000 --> 00:16:23,820
Why don't you two just get back together?

475
00:16:23,940 --> 00:16:25,960
It's great for Sister Jing's image.

476
00:16:26,019 --> 00:16:27,440
Trending for at least five days.

477
00:16:32,539 --> 00:16:34,299
That's not completely out of the question

478
00:16:35,860 --> 00:16:36,960
I'm mainly thinking about

479
00:16:36,960 --> 00:16:38,240
My daughter's career

480
00:16:39,039 --> 00:16:40,480
What are you saying?

481
00:16:40,840 --> 00:16:42,440
Your daughter?

482
00:16:42,620 --> 00:16:44,340
That is *my* daughter

483
00:16:44,419 --> 00:16:46,659
Bai Jingjing's surname is Bai

484
00:16:46,960 --> 00:16:48,240
Think about it carefully

485
00:16:48,259 --> 00:16:49,799
Did you care for her growing up?

486
00:16:49,799 --> 00:16:51,080
What did you ever do for her?

487
00:16:51,080 --> 00:16:52,759
Did you take her to the park?

488
00:16:52,820 --> 00:16:54,480
Or attend her parent-teacher meetings?

489
00:16:54,559 --> 00:16:56,639
Or take her to the children's hospital for shots?

490
00:16:56,659 --> 00:16:59,259
Or go with her to tutoring classes?

491
00:16:59,539 --> 00:17:01,899
It was me who endured the hardships

492
00:17:01,899 --> 00:17:03,779
To raise my daughter into an adult

493
00:17:04,140 --> 00:17:05,359
And make her a big star

494
00:17:05,359 --> 00:17:05,680
You...

495
00:17:05,680 --> 00:17:06,500
Now you show up

496
00:17:06,500 --> 00:17:08,059
You just want to reap the benefits, don't you?

497
00:17:08,240 --> 00:17:09,440
Let me tell you, Liang

498
00:17:09,440 --> 00:17:10,900
You get out of here right now

499
00:17:10,900 --> 00:17:12,779
Don't let me see you again

500
00:17:13,559 --> 00:17:14,180
Look at you

501
00:17:14,180 --> 00:17:15,700
You turn on people just like that

502
00:17:16,180 --> 00:17:17,759
You haven't changed a bit in all these years

503
00:17:17,859 --> 00:17:18,240
I...

504
00:17:18,500 --> 00:17:19,940
I remember it all now too

505
00:17:20,640 --> 00:17:22,240
I was right to leave you back then

506
00:17:22,700 --> 00:17:23,880
I'm going

507
00:17:24,140 --> 00:17:25,200
If I ever come looking for you again...

508
00:17:26,460 --> 00:17:28,240
I wasn't looking for you this time anyway

509
00:17:29,460 --> 00:17:30,720
Didn't I say stop filming?

510
00:17:30,779 --> 00:17:31,500
Delete it all

511
00:17:31,559 --> 00:17:33,319
Or we'll take up the weapon of the law

512
00:17:34,099 --> 00:17:35,299
Everyone knows

513
00:17:35,400 --> 00:17:36,839
If you don't believe me, let's ask Ms. Liu

514
00:17:37,359 --> 00:17:37,980
Ms. Liu

515
00:17:38,440 --> 00:17:40,559
There's a modern poem called *Fragment*

516
00:17:41,119 --> 00:17:41,960
Who is the author?

517
00:17:43,559 --> 00:17:44,420
It's Bian Zhilin, right?

518
00:17:44,420 --> 00:17:45,160
See?

519
00:17:46,480 --> 00:17:47,440
Bian Zhilin

520
00:17:47,500 --> 00:17:48,400
I knew that

521
00:17:48,440 --> 00:17:48,680
Right?

522
00:17:48,680 --> 00:17:49,920
The Hong Kong TV star

523
00:17:50,299 --> 00:17:52,140
You're talking about Guan Zhilin

524
00:17:52,660 --> 00:17:53,240
Mr. Li

525
00:17:54,460 --> 00:17:55,460
The first draft of your memoirs

526
00:17:55,460 --> 00:17:56,319
I've typed it out for you

527
00:17:56,680 --> 00:17:57,619
Here, take a look

528
00:17:58,640 --> 00:17:59,380
Hurry, read it out

529
00:17:59,380 --> 00:17:59,920
Read it

530
00:18:00,000 --> 00:18:01,000
I just love listening to stories

531
00:18:01,000 --> 00:18:01,599
Love listening to stories

532
00:18:01,880 --> 00:18:02,400
Alright

533
00:18:02,680 --> 00:18:03,400
I'll read you a section

534
00:18:04,480 --> 00:18:05,539
Pick an exciting part

535
00:18:10,140 --> 00:18:10,980
How about this part

536
00:18:13,359 --> 00:18:14,799
The year 1997

537
00:18:15,059 --> 00:18:16,559
Was a glorious year

538
00:18:17,299 --> 00:18:19,220
At the time, with great foresight

539
00:18:19,279 --> 00:18:20,500
I overcame all dissenting opinions

540
00:18:20,579 --> 00:18:22,559
Financial investment, planning approval

541
00:18:22,640 --> 00:18:23,940
I ran my legs off

542
00:18:23,980 --> 00:18:25,299
I wore out my lips talking

543
00:18:25,359 --> 00:18:27,680
Finally, in the place where I once fought

544
00:18:27,740 --> 00:18:30,519
A Sanjiang Bridge rose from the ground

545
00:18:30,579 --> 00:18:32,880
It was truly a bridge flying north and south

546
00:18:32,920 --> 00:18:34,819
Turning a deep chasm into a thoroughfare

547
00:18:35,319 --> 00:18:36,339
Keep blowing

548
00:18:36,339 --> 00:18:37,519
You're blowing it out of proportion

549
00:18:38,359 --> 00:18:40,559
I'm not blowing, this is real

550
00:18:40,680 --> 00:18:41,319
Mr. Li

551
00:18:41,859 --> 00:18:43,220
When we write an autobiography

552
00:18:43,480 --> 00:18:44,819
We must seek truth from facts

553
00:18:44,819 --> 00:18:45,640
It is not suitable

554
00:18:45,720 --> 00:18:47,140
To exaggerate too much

555
00:18:48,059 --> 00:18:49,240
I didn't exaggerate

556
00:18:49,400 --> 00:18:50,119
Not exaggeration

557
00:18:50,180 --> 00:18:51,079
It's pure fabrication

558
00:18:52,640 --> 00:18:53,059
I...

559
00:18:53,460 --> 00:18:54,680
I have a witness

560
00:18:55,240 --> 00:18:57,140
The Chief Engineer back then, Hu Yuguang

561
00:18:57,299 --> 00:18:58,339
Was my old subordinate

562
00:18:58,539 --> 00:18:59,299
A good partner

563
00:18:59,539 --> 00:19:00,880
He can testify for me

564
00:19:01,539 --> 00:19:02,579
A bear harvesting corn

565
00:19:02,579 --> 00:19:03,279
Pure nonsense

566
00:19:05,740 --> 00:19:06,579
You don't believe me, right?

567
00:19:08,559 --> 00:19:10,579
Tomorrow I'll go find Chief Engineer Hu

568
00:19:10,920 --> 00:19:12,079
And verify

569
00:19:12,079 --> 00:19:13,619
Some of the technical details from back then

570
00:19:14,160 --> 00:19:14,779
Yusheng

571
00:19:15,480 --> 00:19:16,400
Come with me tomorrow

572
00:19:17,380 --> 00:19:18,460
Be my witness

573
00:19:18,900 --> 00:19:20,039
Use facts

574
00:19:20,279 --> 00:19:21,640
To strike back at his

575
00:19:22,559 --> 00:19:23,440
Cynical mockery

576
00:19:35,039 --> 00:19:35,759
Come in.

577
00:19:40,140 --> 00:19:41,019
Xiao Hu.

578
00:19:41,240 --> 00:19:42,440
Long time no see.

579
00:19:45,140 --> 00:19:46,380
Who is this?

580
00:19:46,839 --> 00:19:48,259
Mr. Know-It-All.

581
00:19:49,339 --> 00:19:49,920
President Li.

582
00:19:50,160 --> 00:19:50,640
President Li.

583
00:19:51,700 --> 00:19:52,740
Don't call me President Li.

584
00:19:52,920 --> 00:19:53,539
I'm retired.

585
00:19:56,480 --> 00:19:57,240
Xiao Hu.

586
00:19:58,240 --> 00:19:58,880
No.

587
00:19:59,359 --> 00:20:00,200
Old Hu.

588
00:20:01,200 --> 00:20:01,819
President Hu.

589
00:20:03,299 --> 00:20:04,299
How have you been lately?

590
00:20:04,640 --> 00:20:05,400
Doing great.

591
00:20:06,579 --> 00:20:08,160
Not working with you anymore,

592
00:20:08,259 --> 00:20:09,220
how could I not be?

593
00:20:11,000 --> 00:20:11,940
Uncle.

594
00:20:12,180 --> 00:20:13,900
How can you say that?

595
00:20:14,359 --> 00:20:15,539
That's just too...

596
00:20:15,740 --> 00:20:16,839
rude, isn't it?

597
00:20:17,940 --> 00:20:18,599
Handsome.

598
00:20:19,500 --> 00:20:21,200
If you knew how we used to

599
00:20:21,839 --> 00:20:22,900
work together back then,

600
00:20:22,900 --> 00:20:23,880
you wouldn't say that.

601
00:20:25,660 --> 00:20:26,680
I do know.

602
00:20:27,539 --> 00:20:28,720
Back in '97,

603
00:20:28,720 --> 00:20:29,759
it was you and President Li

604
00:20:29,759 --> 00:20:31,259
who built the Sanjiang Bridge together.

605
00:20:31,940 --> 00:20:32,900
At the time, President Li

606
00:20:33,000 --> 00:20:33,940
showed great foresight,

607
00:20:34,039 --> 00:20:35,160
overruled all objections,

608
00:20:35,259 --> 00:20:37,160
and fully supported your design and construction.

609
00:20:37,539 --> 00:20:38,680
You two...

610
00:20:38,839 --> 00:20:40,700
weren't you great partners at work?

611
00:20:40,880 --> 00:20:42,140
Is that how you tricked him?

612
00:20:42,220 --> 00:20:43,259
Yeah, that's how I tricked...

613
00:20:43,539 --> 00:20:44,680
No, how is that a trick?

614
00:20:45,279 --> 00:20:46,839
It's the honest truth!

615
00:20:47,140 --> 00:20:48,119
How come you don't remember?

616
00:20:48,380 --> 00:20:50,180
How can I remember something that never happened?

617
00:20:51,500 --> 00:20:53,380
Back then, you were clearly giving blind orders.

618
00:20:53,440 --> 00:20:54,779
An amateur leading the expert.

619
00:20:55,400 --> 00:20:57,019
Why do you think I changed jobs later?

620
00:20:57,579 --> 00:20:59,099
Why did I come to this company?

621
00:20:59,500 --> 00:21:00,500
It's all his fault.

622
00:21:00,880 --> 00:21:02,319
How is it my fault?

623
00:21:03,700 --> 00:21:05,000
That project back then,

624
00:21:05,339 --> 00:21:06,480
we were on the same team.

625
00:21:06,480 --> 00:21:07,039
That part is true.

626
00:21:07,039 --> 00:21:07,839
See? Right?

627
00:21:08,839 --> 00:21:09,799
But... however...

628
00:21:11,539 --> 00:21:12,880
I said right from the start,

629
00:21:13,000 --> 00:21:14,500
the geological conditions there

630
00:21:14,559 --> 00:21:15,880
weren't suitable for building a bridge.

631
00:21:15,880 --> 00:21:16,700
Did I say that or not?

632
00:21:19,500 --> 00:21:20,640
Seems like that happened.

633
00:21:21,720 --> 00:21:22,859
But that project of ours

634
00:21:22,859 --> 00:21:24,660
was to benefit the local people!

635
00:21:24,660 --> 00:21:26,160
Give me a break.

636
00:21:26,299 --> 00:21:27,279
Actually, he...

637
00:21:27,279 --> 00:21:29,160
just wanted to show off

638
00:21:29,160 --> 00:21:30,480
in front of the locals.

639
00:21:30,539 --> 00:21:33,279
Actually, the geological conditions 10km away

640
00:21:33,319 --> 00:21:34,619
were much better for a bridge.

641
00:21:34,660 --> 00:21:35,940
And the people in that county

642
00:21:36,200 --> 00:21:38,019
really needed that bridge too.

643
00:21:40,240 --> 00:21:41,339
So what?

644
00:21:42,339 --> 00:21:43,480
I was a senior executive.

645
00:21:43,519 --> 00:21:45,160
I fully listened to

646
00:21:45,200 --> 00:21:46,799
opinions from all sides

647
00:21:47,039 --> 00:21:48,559
before resolutely making the final call

648
00:21:48,619 --> 00:21:49,839
to build the bridge at the original site.

649
00:21:49,920 --> 00:21:50,579
Great foresight,

650
00:21:50,579 --> 00:21:51,519
overruling objections, right?

651
00:21:53,539 --> 00:21:55,299
It's true you were an executive.

652
00:21:55,819 --> 00:21:56,640
But you can't just

653
00:21:56,640 --> 00:21:58,180
meddle in everything blindly.

654
00:21:58,539 --> 00:21:59,299
Do you know

655
00:21:59,480 --> 00:22:01,240
what we call him in private?

656
00:22:02,500 --> 00:22:03,599
Mr. Know-It-All.

657
00:22:03,740 --> 00:22:04,740
Fine.

658
00:22:05,019 --> 00:22:05,640
Enough.

659
00:22:06,200 --> 00:22:07,339
Stop spreading that around.

660
00:22:09,119 --> 00:22:11,420
Every place has a few backward folks.

661
00:22:11,500 --> 00:22:12,160
Right?

662
00:22:12,839 --> 00:22:13,859
Let's get back to work.

663
00:22:14,819 --> 00:22:16,240
After that project was built,

664
00:22:16,799 --> 00:22:18,400
didn't it benefit the locals?

665
00:22:18,720 --> 00:22:20,519
The company also made a profit.

666
00:22:21,000 --> 00:22:22,700
Half the credit goes to you.

667
00:22:22,880 --> 00:22:24,579
Shouldn't half of it be mine too?

668
00:22:25,859 --> 00:22:27,319
I had no part in a lot of it.

669
00:22:28,500 --> 00:22:29,180
Let me ask you.

670
00:22:29,839 --> 00:22:32,299
That construction team for the bridge contract...

671
00:22:32,599 --> 00:22:33,660
...you decided on them, right?

672
00:22:33,839 --> 00:22:35,240
That foreman, Liu Big Head...

673
00:22:35,400 --> 00:22:36,400
...is an acquaintance of yours, right?

674
00:22:37,279 --> 00:22:38,900
No, his grandfather and I were close.

675
00:22:39,140 --> 00:22:40,059
I introduced him.

676
00:22:40,339 --> 00:22:40,960
But...

677
00:22:41,799 --> 00:22:43,019
...his construction team...

678
00:22:43,240 --> 00:22:45,240
...was seriously underqualified.

679
00:22:45,559 --> 00:22:46,119
Also...

680
00:22:46,720 --> 00:22:47,460
...the project budget...

681
00:22:47,920 --> 00:22:49,140
...you had the final say, right?

682
00:22:49,299 --> 00:22:49,859
Of course.

683
00:22:50,559 --> 00:22:51,700
I'm the head of the company.

684
00:22:53,359 --> 00:22:54,619
My original design...

685
00:22:54,839 --> 00:22:56,099
...was sturdy and durable.

686
00:22:56,099 --> 00:22:57,200
And cost-effective.

687
00:22:57,720 --> 00:22:58,400
But him?

688
00:22:58,480 --> 00:22:59,980
He just had to meddle in it.

689
00:23:00,140 --> 00:23:01,799
Nitpicking everything.

690
00:23:01,839 --> 00:23:04,019
The bridge was nearly half built...

691
00:23:04,220 --> 00:23:06,099
...and he insisted on tearing it down and starting over.

692
00:23:06,359 --> 00:23:07,059
And what happened in the end?

693
00:23:07,400 --> 00:23:08,559
The budget ran out.

694
00:23:08,680 --> 00:23:10,420
We had to cut corners.

695
00:23:10,700 --> 00:23:11,500
Finally...

696
00:23:12,460 --> 00:23:13,680
...it became a tofu-dreg project.

697
00:23:15,839 --> 00:23:16,700
Grandpa Li...

698
00:23:17,339 --> 00:23:18,619
...is this true?

699
00:23:20,799 --> 00:23:22,140
Why is this completely different...

700
00:23:22,140 --> 00:23:24,000
...from what I remember?

701
00:23:25,359 --> 00:23:26,019
Handsome...

702
00:23:26,839 --> 00:23:28,160
...do you still think...

703
00:23:28,460 --> 00:23:29,539
...I'm being rude to him?

704
00:23:32,359 --> 00:23:33,980
How could it be like this?

705
00:23:35,140 --> 00:23:36,259
But regardless...

706
00:23:36,579 --> 00:23:38,440
...from a young novice...

707
00:23:39,099 --> 00:23:40,279
...if not for me...

708
00:23:40,839 --> 00:23:41,940
...if not for this project...

709
00:23:42,460 --> 00:23:44,900
...would you have been fast-tracked to Chief Engineer?

710
00:23:45,519 --> 00:23:47,480
You should at least thank me for that.

711
00:23:47,700 --> 00:23:48,299
Yes.

712
00:23:49,599 --> 00:23:51,319
I'm especially grateful to you.

713
00:23:52,740 --> 00:23:53,440
The year before last...

714
00:23:54,539 --> 00:23:56,740
...it rained for days, and flash floods hit.

715
00:23:56,819 --> 00:23:57,680
That bridge...

716
00:23:59,160 --> 00:23:59,980
...collapsed.

717
00:24:01,480 --> 00:24:01,960
Collapsed.

718
00:24:02,920 --> 00:24:05,279
Luckily, there were no casualties.

719
00:24:06,099 --> 00:24:07,119
Later, when they investigated...

720
00:24:08,000 --> 00:24:09,119
...who designed this bridge?

721
00:24:09,900 --> 00:24:10,400
Well, there it is.

722
00:24:11,599 --> 00:24:12,480
So...

723
00:24:12,640 --> 00:24:13,640
...I changed jobs...

724
00:24:14,000 --> 00:24:15,299
...and came here to do administration.

725
00:24:16,559 --> 00:24:18,779
I'm especially grateful for that bridge.

726
00:24:19,680 --> 00:24:20,799
Thank you, Mr. Li.

727
00:24:21,400 --> 00:24:23,059
For giving me this black mark on my record.

728
00:24:27,500 --> 00:24:29,000
How could it be like this?

729
00:24:31,160 --> 00:24:34,000
Seems memory is quite unreliable.

730
00:24:36,140 --> 00:24:36,720
Mr. Hu...

731
00:24:37,319 --> 00:24:39,259
...I completely understand you now.

732
00:24:40,140 --> 00:24:42,819
I just hope when I start working...

733
00:24:44,099 --> 00:24:44,579
...I don't run into...

734
00:24:44,579 --> 00:24:46,920
...a boss like Grandpa Li.

735
00:24:47,619 --> 00:24:48,400
Why are you like this?

736
00:24:49,140 --> 00:24:50,000
Whose side are you on?

737
00:24:50,279 --> 00:24:50,799
I...

738
00:24:53,099 --> 00:24:54,059
He has a point.

739
00:24:59,220 --> 00:24:59,839
What happened next?

740
00:25:01,140 --> 00:25:01,920
Brother Liang.

741
00:25:02,039 --> 00:25:03,779
You're not writing your memoirs anymore?

742
00:25:04,559 --> 00:25:05,119
Not anymore.

743
00:25:05,940 --> 00:25:08,099
Professor Fan is right about this.

744
00:25:08,220 --> 00:25:09,240
We are still young.

745
00:25:09,660 --> 00:25:11,079
No rush to write memoirs.

746
00:25:12,240 --> 00:25:13,000
Grandpa Li.

747
00:25:13,380 --> 00:25:15,000
Are you getting rid of all these drafts?

748
00:25:15,539 --> 00:25:16,400
Shred them all.

749
00:25:16,480 --> 00:25:17,240
Don't leave a single word.

750
00:25:18,240 --> 00:25:20,599
So *Jianguo's Memoirs* is halted too?

751
00:25:22,339 --> 00:25:23,500
Through this recollection,

752
00:25:24,880 --> 00:25:26,319
I realized many past events

753
00:25:26,440 --> 00:25:28,259
don't match my memory,

754
00:25:28,660 --> 00:25:30,160
or are even the exact opposite.

755
00:25:30,680 --> 00:25:32,700
Many were just things I imagined.

756
00:25:33,000 --> 00:25:33,619
So,

757
00:25:33,740 --> 00:25:35,180
I decided not to write it.

758
00:25:35,299 --> 00:25:36,599
Scrap it and start over.

759
00:25:37,980 --> 00:25:38,839
Seek truth from facts.

760
00:25:38,900 --> 00:25:39,619
Verify carefully.

761
00:25:39,940 --> 00:25:41,460
Even the embarrassing stuff,

762
00:25:41,460 --> 00:25:42,400
I will write it all down.

763
00:25:42,940 --> 00:25:44,039
To warn future generations.

764
00:25:44,480 --> 00:25:44,880
Yes.

765
00:25:45,000 --> 00:25:45,420
Good.

766
00:25:45,480 --> 00:25:46,019
Right?

767
00:25:47,059 --> 00:25:49,119
Professor Fan, what are you strolling around for?

768
00:25:49,599 --> 00:25:50,559
Writing my memoirs.

769
00:25:50,559 --> 00:25:52,059
I need to trace back some details.

770
00:25:52,059 --> 00:25:53,259
I came out to clear my head.

771
00:25:53,779 --> 00:25:54,180
You...

772
00:25:54,240 --> 00:25:56,579
Didn't you say you weren't in a rush to write them?

773
00:25:56,779 --> 00:25:58,079
I thought about it again.

774
00:25:59,000 --> 00:26:00,980
My precious life experiences

775
00:26:01,339 --> 00:26:03,339
should be salvaged and excavated.

776
00:26:03,380 --> 00:26:04,420
Left for the future

777
00:26:04,539 --> 00:26:05,500
generations of students.

778
00:26:05,599 --> 00:26:07,059
I expect it will cause

779
00:26:07,319 --> 00:26:08,779
quite a sensation in the academic world.

780
00:26:09,519 --> 00:26:10,759
This guy is bragging again.

781
00:26:10,759 --> 00:26:11,319
Tell me,

782
00:26:11,380 --> 00:26:12,559
why is he like this?

783
00:26:12,640 --> 00:26:13,940
Probably caught it from you.

784
00:26:13,940 --> 00:26:14,420
Right.

785
00:26:14,539 --> 00:26:15,480
Who?

786
00:26:15,839 --> 00:26:16,519
Everyone,

787
00:26:16,799 --> 00:26:17,940
my memoirs

788
00:26:18,220 --> 00:26:20,079
will start from the resumption of the entrance exams.

789
00:26:20,440 --> 00:26:22,099
That was the turning point of my life.

790
00:26:22,500 --> 00:26:24,279
The fighting year of 1977.

791
00:26:24,319 --> 00:26:25,880
I stepped onto the university campus.

792
00:26:26,099 --> 00:26:26,680
Hold on.

793
00:26:27,980 --> 00:26:29,039
Which year did you say?

794
00:26:29,359 --> 00:26:30,579
1977.

795
00:26:30,759 --> 00:26:31,720
I'm Class of '77.

796
00:26:31,900 --> 00:26:32,619
The first batch.

797
00:26:32,720 --> 00:26:33,180
Wrong.

798
00:26:34,259 --> 00:26:36,160
You students of the Class of '77

799
00:26:36,680 --> 00:26:38,720
passed the exam in '77,

800
00:26:38,900 --> 00:26:40,740
but entered campus in '78.

801
00:26:41,119 --> 00:26:42,319
How is that possible?

802
00:26:42,539 --> 00:26:43,680
Don't mess with my train of thought.

803
00:26:43,680 --> 00:26:44,920
I have to go continue writing.

804
00:26:44,920 --> 00:26:45,680
1978.

805
00:26:45,880 --> 00:26:47,160
Must stick to the facts.

806
00:26:47,799 --> 00:26:48,579
1978.

807
00:26:49,259 --> 00:26:50,720
Another Muddlehead.
